import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['state', 'population']]
    data = data.groupby('state').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('population', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['population'], color='c')
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'], c=data['id'], cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Population')
    ax.set_ylabel('Engineers')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the number of engineers and population in each state?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="States")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the frequency of hurricanes in each state?', wrap=True)

    plt.ylabel('Frequency of Hurricanes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
